```json
    "filename_ext": ".st",
    "code": "Object subclass: #BinarySearchTree
    instanceVariableNames: 'value left right'
    classVariableNames: ''
    poolDictionaries: ''
    category: 'Collections-Trees'!

!BinarySearchTree class methodsFor: 'instance creation'!
new
    ^super new initialize!

withValue: aValue
    ^self new value: aValue; yourself
! !

!BinarySearchTree methodsFor: 'initialization'!
initialize
    left := nil.
    right := nil.
    value := nil.
! !

!BinarySearchTree methodsFor: 'accessing'!
value
    ^value!

value: aValue
    value := aValue!

left
    ^left!

right
    ^right
! !

!BinarySearchTree methodsFor: 'operations'!
insert: aValue
    value isNil ifTrue: [
        value := aValue.
        ^self
    ].
    
    aValue < value ifTrue: [
        left isNil ifTrue: [
            left := BinarySearchTree withValue: aValue
        ] ifFalse: [
            left insert: aValue
        ]
    ] ifFalse: [
        aValue > value ifTrue: [
            right isNil ifTrue: [
                right := BinarySearchTree withValue: aValue
            ] ifFalse: [
                right insert: aValue
            ]
        ]
    ]!

search: aValue
    value isNil ifTrue: [^false].
    aValue = value ifTrue: [^true].
    
    aValue < value ifTrue: [
        ^left notNil and: [left search: aValue]
    ] ifFalse: [
        ^right notNil and: [right search: aValue]
    ]!

inOrder: aBlock
    left notNil ifTrue: [left inOrder: aBlock].
    value notNil ifTrue: [aBlock value: value].
    right notNil ifTrue: [right inOrder: aBlock]
! !",
    "license_guess": "GFDL"
  }
}
```

		end

feature -- Output

		do
			if attached root as r then

		end

```json
    root isNil
```

{

    "name": "Cobra",
    "aliases": ["Cobra.NET"],
    "evidence_url": "https://cobra-language.com/"
  },
  "program": {
    "title": "Simple Cobra Game Class Example",
    "origin_url": "https://cobra-language.com/docs/hello/",
    "filename_ext": ".cobra",
    "code": "class Game
    def run
        print 'Welcome!'
        numGuesses = 0
        magicNum = Random.next(1, 11)  # 1 to 10
        while true
            print
            print 'Enter your guess (1-10) or 0 to quit:'
            guess = Console.readLine
            if guess == '0'
                break
            numGuesses += 1
            n = int.parse(guess)
            if n == magicNum
                print 'You got it!'
                break
            else if n < magicNum
                print 'Higher.'
            else
                print 'Lower.'
        print 'It took you [numGuesses] guesses.'",
    "license_guess": null
  }
}

    "name": "CLIPS",

  }
}

```json
    "code": "class
	BINARY_SEARCH_TREE [G -> COMPARABLE]

create
	make

feature {NONE} -- Initialization

	make
			-- Create an empty tree.
		do
			create root
		end

feature -- Access

	root: detachable BINARY_SEARCH_TREE_NODE [G]
			-- Root node of the tree

feature -- Element change

	insert (v: G)
			-- Insert `v' into the tree.
		do
			if attached root as r then
				r.insert (v)
			else
				create root.make (v)
			end
		end

feature -- Status report

	has (v: G): BOOLEAN
			-- Does the tree contain `v'?
		do
			if attached root as r then
				Result := r.has (v)
			end
		end

feature -- Output

	print_tree
			-- Print the tree in order.
		do
			if attached root as r then
				r.print_in_order
			end
			io.put_new_line
		end

end",

  }
}
```

```json
create
    make

    make
            -- Create an empty tree.
        do
            root := Void
        end

feature -- Access

    root: detachable TREE_NODE [G]
            -- Root node of the tree

    has (v: G): BOOLEAN
            -- Does tree contain `v'?
        do
            Result := has_node (root, v)
        end

feature -- Element change

    insert (v: G)
            -- Insert `v' into tree.
        do
            root := insert_node (root, v)
        end

feature -- Output

    traverse
            -- Print tree in order.
        do
            traverse_node (root)
        end

feature {NONE} -- Implementation

    has_node (node: detachable TREE_NODE [G]; v: G): BOOLEAN
            -- Does `node' contain `v'?
        do
            if node /= Void then
                if v < node.value then
                    Result := has_node (node.left, v)
                elseif v > node.value then
                    Result := has_node (node.right, v)
                else
                    Result := True
                end
            end
        end

    insert_node (node: detachable TREE_NODE [G]; v: G): TREE_NODE [G]
            -- Insert `v' into `node' and return new root.

            if node = Void then

                node.set_left (insert_node (node.left, v))

                node.set_right (insert_node (node.right, v))
                Result := node
            else

            end
```

{
  "language": {
    "name": "CLIPS",
    "aliases": ["C Language Integrated Production System"],
    "evidence_url": "https://www.clipsrules.net/"
  },
  "program": {
    "title": "Expert System for Car Diagnosis",
    "origin_url": "https://github.com/timm/tested/blob/main/etc/clips/car.clp",
    "filename_ext": ".clp",
    "code": "(deffacts initial-facts
   (working-state start))

(defrule determine-engine-state
   ?w <- (working-state start)
   =>
   (retract ?w)
   (printout t "Does the engine start (yes/no)? ")
   (assert (engine-starts (read))))

(defrule determine-engine-quality
   (engine-starts yes)
   ?w <- (working-state start)
   =>
   (retract ?w)
   (printout t "How is the engine running (rough/smooth)? ")
   (assert (engine-quality (read))))

(defrule normal-engine-state
   (engine-starts yes)
   (engine-quality smooth)
   =>
   (printout t "Your engine is running fine." crlf))

(defrule rough-engine-state
   (engine-starts yes)
   (engine-quality rough)
   =>
   (printout t "Your engine needs a tune up." crlf))",
    "license_guess": "MIT"
  }
}

)abbrev domain UP UnivariatePolynomial
UnivariatePolynomial(R : Ring, var : Symbol) : Exports == Implementation where
  Exports ==> PolynomialCategory(R, SingletonAsOrderedSet var, NonNegativeInteger)
  Implementation ==> add
    Rep := SparseUnivariatePolynomial R
    coerce(p : %) : OutputForm ==
      empty? p => 0::OutputForm
      degree p = 0 => leadingCoefficient(p)::OutputForm
      sum : OutputForm := 0
      for i in 0..degree p | not zero? coefficient(p, i) repeat
        ci := coefficient(p, i)::OutputForm
        if i = 0 then sum := sum + ci
        else if ci = 1 then
          if i = 1 then sum := sum + var::OutputForm
          else sum := sum + (var::OutputForm ** i::OutputForm)
        else
          if i = 1 then sum := sum + (ci * var::OutputForm)
          else sum := sum + (ci * (var::OutputForm ** i::OutputForm))

```json
{
  "language": {
    "name": "Rebol",
    "aliases": ["REBOL"],
    "evidence_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rebol"
  },
  "program": {
    "title": "Simple HTTP Server",
    "origin_url": "https://github.com/gchiu/rebolbot/blob/master/httpd.r",
    "filename_ext": ".r",
    "code": "REBOL [
    Title: "Simple HTTP Server"
    Date: 20-Jul-2009
    File: %httpd.r
    Author: "Carl Sassenrath"
    Purpose: "A tiny HTTP server."
]

html-page: func [data] [
    rejoin [
        "HTTP/1.0 200 OK^/Content-type: text/html^/^/"
        "<html><body>" data "</body></html>"
    ]
]

handle-request: func [client /local data path file] [
    data: copy ""
    while [not find data "^/^/"] [
        append data copy client
    ]
    parse data ["GET " copy path to " " to end]
    path: to-file next path
    either exists? path [
        if find [%.r %.reb] suffix? path [
            do path
            insert client html-page "Script executed."
            return
        ]
        file: read/binary path
        insert client rejoin [
            "HTTP/1.0 200 OK^/Content-type: " "application/octet-stream" "^/^/"
        ]
        insert client file
    ][
        insert client html-page "File not found."
    ]
]

server-port: open/lines tcp://:8080

forever [
    client: first server-port
    handle-request client
    close client
]",
    "license_guess": null
  }
}
```

	make

			create root
		end

	root: detachable BINARY_SEARCH_TREE_NODE [G]

	insert (v: G)
			-- Insert `v' into the tree.

			else
				create root.make (v)
			end
		end

				Result := r.has (v)

			else
				if attached right as r then
					r.insert (v)
				else
					create right.make (v)
				end
			end
		end

	has (v: G): BOOLEAN

		do
			if v = value then
				Result := True
			elseif v < value then
				if attached left as l then
					Result := l.has (v)
				end
			else
				if attached right as r then
					Result := r.has (v)
				end
			end

```json
{
  "language": {
    "name": "Rebol",
    "aliases": ["REBOL"],
    "evidence_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rebol"
  },
  "program": {
    "title": "Simple HTTP Server",
    "origin_url": "https://github.com/gchiu/rebolbot/blob/master/httpd.r",
    "filename_ext": ".r",
    "code": "REBOL [
    Title: "Simple HTTP Server"
    Date: 20-Jul-2009
    File: %httpd.r
    Author: "Carl Sassenrath"
    Purpose: "A tiny HTTP server."
]

html-page: func [data] [
    rejoin [
        "HTTP/1.0 200 OK^/Content-type: text/html^/^/"
        "<html><body>" data "</body></html>"
    ]
]

handle-request: func [client /local data path] [
    data: make string! 1020
    copy/part data client 1020
    parse data ["GET " copy path to " " to end]
    path: to-file next path
    if path = %"" [path: %index.html]
    either exists? path [
        insert data read path
        insert data "HTTP/1.0 200 OK^/Content-type: text/html^/^/"
    ][
        data: html-page ["File not found: " path]
    ]
    insert client data
    close client
]

server-port: open/lines tcp://:8080

forever [
    client: first server-port
    handle-request client
]",
    "license_guess": null
  }
}
```
